item.title: Error fix?
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

You placed the String before the class declaration.
Example:

public static String UUID;
public class HelloWorld{

     public static void main(String []args){
        System.out.println("Hello World");
     }
}

I compiled that and got:

javac HelloWorld.java HelloWorld.java:2: error: class, interface, or enum expected public static String UUID; ^ 1 error

And the fix:

[code=java]
public class HelloWorld{
public static String UUID;

 public static void main(String []args){
    System.out.println("Hello World");
 }

}[/code]
